{{Refimprove|date=May 2017}}
'''Organic clothing''' is clothing made from materials raised in or grown in compliance with [[Organic agriculture|organic agricultural]] standards.{{Citation needed|date=July 2009}} Organic clothing may be composed of [[Cotton]], [[Jute]], [[Silk]], [[Ramie]], or [[Wool]]. Textiles do not need to be 100% organic to use the organic label.<ref>{{cite web|title=Policy Memorandum|url=https://www.ams.usda.gov/sites/default/files/media/NOP-PM-11-14-LabelingofTextiles.pdf|publisher=USDA (May 20 2011)|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> A more general term is ''organic textiles'', which includes both apparel and home textiles. The technical requirements in terms of certification and origin generally remain same for organic clothing and organic textiles.
