{{italic title}} [[File:Bohumil_Kubišta_-_St_Sebastian.jpg|thumb|right]] '''''St Sebastian''''' is a 20th-century painting by the Bohemian artist [[Bohumil Kubišta]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.europeana.eu/portal/record/2063619/CZR_280_006.html|title=St Sebastian, 1912|website=www.europeana.eu|access-date=2016-05-03}}</ref> [[Saint Sebastian]] was a Christian matryr. It is held in the [[National Gallery in Prague]].
The picture is painted on in oils on canvas and has dimensions of 98 x 74,5&nbsp;cm. It is one of the most important works of Bohumil Kubishta, member of the pre-First World War Czech avant-garde. Unlike traditional Christian interpretations of the theme of suffering of the Christian martyr, Bohumil Kubishta combines cubist forms and expressiveness, but integrates spiritual strength.<ref name=":0" />
